SELECT
  (i.invoice_number->>'value')::text AS invoice_number,
  (i.invoice_date->>'value')::text AS invoice_date,
  (i.due_date->>'value')::text AS due_date,
  (i.total->>'value')::numeric AS invoice_total,
  (i.sub_total->>'value')::numeric AS sub_total,
  (i.tax->>'value')::numeric AS tax,
  (i.discount->>'value')::numeric AS discount,
  (i.freight_charges->>'value')::numeric AS freight_charges,
  (i.other_charges->>'value')::numeric AS other_charges,
  (i.credit_and_returns->>'value')::numeric AS credit_and_returns,
  (v.name) AS vendor_name,
  (v.company) AS vendor_company,
  (v.address) AS vendor_address,
  (v.city->>'value') AS vendor_city,
  (v.state->>'value') AS vendor_state,
  (v.zip->>'value') AS vendor_zip,
  (v.country->>'value') AS vendor_country,
  current_date - (i.due_date->>'value')::date AS days_overdue,

    WHEN current_date - (i.due_date->>'value')::date <= 30 THEN '0-30 days'
    WHEN current_date - (i.due_date->>'value')::date <= 60 THEN '31-60 days'
    WHEN current_date - (i.due_date->>'value')::date <= 90 THEN '61-90 days'

  END AS age_bucket
FROM icap_invoice i
LEFT JOIN icap_vendor v ON i.vendor_id = v.id
WHERE (i.due_date->>'value')::date < current_date
ORDER BY days_overdue;
